<p>The board’s non-executive member is the chair of the Audit Committee. Another member of the Audit Committee attends the Board as a non-executive member.</p>

<p>In addition, the <abbr title="Joint Management Board">JMB</abbr> has 3 sub-committees.</p>

<h2 id="audit-committee">Audit Committee</h2>

<p>The Audit Committee provides assurance and advice to the Director as Principal Accounting Officer on the Offices’ management of resources and management of risk.</p>

<p>The Audit Committee is advised by the National Audit Office and by Internal Audit of the Ministry of Justice.</p>

<p>Read the terms of reference of the Committee:</p>

<p><span id="attachment_2336386" class="attachment-inline">
  <a href="/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/461004/Terms-of-Reference-Document-SOOAGAC-10.doc">Terms of Reference</a>
  (<span class="type">MS Word Document</span>, <span class="file-size">59.5KB</span>)
</span></p>

<p>The annual report of the Audit Committee is published as an annex to the full annual report.</p>

<h2 id="scotland-senior-management-team-and-oag-senior-management-team">Scotland Senior Management Team and <abbr title="Office of the Advocate General">OAG</abbr> Senior Management Team</h2>

<p>Senior Management Teams deal with operational matters within the offices.</p>

<p>Our only arms length body is the <a rel="external" href="http://www.bcomm-scotland.independent.gov.uk/">Boundary Commission for Scotland</a>.</p>

